#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="an10.171"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an10.171:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 10 "
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 10 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an10.171:0.2"
msgid "17. Jāṇussoṇivagga "
msgstr "17. With Jāṇussoṇi "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "an10.171:0.3"
msgid "171. Paṭhamaadhammasutta "
msgstr "171. Bad Principles (1st) "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc1
msgctxt "an10.171:1.1"
msgid "“Adhammo ca, bhikkhave, veditabbo anattho ca; "
msgstr "“Mendicants, you should know bad principles with bad results. "

msgctxt "an10.171:1.2"
msgid "dhammo ca veditabbo attho ca. "
msgstr "And you should know good principles with good results. "

msgctxt "an10.171:1.3"
msgid "Adhammañca viditvā anatthañca, dhammañca viditvā atthañca yathā dhammo yathā attho tathā paṭipajjitabbaṃ. "
msgstr "Knowing these things, your practice should follow the good principles with good results. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "an10.171:2.1"
msgid "Katamo ca, bhikkhave, adhammo ca anattho ca? "
msgstr "And what are bad principles with bad results? "

msgctxt "an10.171:2.2"
msgid "Pāṇātipāto, adinnādānaṃ, kāmesumicchācāro, musāvādo, pisuṇā vācā, pharusā vācā, samphappalāpo, abhijjhā, byāpādo, micchādiṭṭhi—"
msgstr "Killing living creatures, stealing, and sexual misconduct; speech that’s false, divisive, harsh, or nonsensical; covetousness, ill will, and wrong view. "

msgctxt "an10.171:2.3"
msgid "ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, adhammo ca anattho ca. "
msgstr "These are called bad principles with bad results. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "an10.171:3.1"
msgid "Katamo ca, bhikkhave, dhammo ca attho ca? "
msgstr "And what are good principles with good results? "

msgctxt "an10.171:3.2"
msgid "Pāṇātipātā veramaṇī, adinnādānā veramaṇī, kāmesumicchācārā veramaṇī, musāvādā veramaṇī, pisuṇāya vācāya veramaṇī, pharusāya vācāya veramaṇī, samphappalāpā veramaṇī, anabhijjhā, abyāpādo, sammādiṭṭhi—"
msgstr "Avoiding killing living creatures, stealing, and sexual misconduct; avoiding speech that’s false, divisive, harsh, or nonsensical; contentment, good will, and right view. "

msgctxt "an10.171:3.3"
msgid "ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, dhammo ca attho ca. "
msgstr "These are called good principles with good results. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc4
msgctxt "an10.171:4.1"
msgid "‘Adhammo ca, bhikkhave, veditabbo anattho ca; "
msgstr "‘You should know bad principles with bad results. "

msgctxt "an10.171:4.2"
msgid "dhammo ca veditabbo attho ca. "
msgstr "And you should know good principles with good results. "

msgctxt "an10.171:4.3"
msgid "Adhammañca viditvā anatthañca, dhammañca viditvā atthañca yathā dhammo yathā attho tathā paṭipajjitabban’ti, "
msgstr "Knowing these things, your practice should follow the good principles with good results.’ "

msgctxt "an10.171:4.4"
msgid "iti yaṃ taṃ vuttaṃ, idametaṃ paṭicca vuttan”ti. "
msgstr "That’s what I said, and this is why I said it.” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an10.171:4.5"
msgid "Pañcamaṃ. "
msgstr ""

#. HTML: </p></article></section></body></html>
